[[{"text": ["You can try django.", "It has forms module, that provides many useful mechanisms for web forms."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "django", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "forms", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 1, "childList": []}]}], [{"text": ["There's also web.py's Form class which you may find interesting.", "There are examples in its cookbook."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "web.py", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://webpy.org/"}, {"text": "cookbook", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://webpy.org/cookbook/"}]}], [{"text": ["You might check out web2py, which provides several mechanisms for generating and processing forms (see also form-related Javascript and Ajax functionality).", "Its form objects (and other HTML helper objects) are server-side representations of the HTML DOM and can be manipulated prior to serialization into HTML (see ref1, ref2, ref3, ref4).", "If you have further questions about it, ask on the mailing list."], "childNum": 8, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "web2py", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.web2py.com"}, {"text": "generating and processing forms", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://web2py.com/book/default/chapter/07"}, {"text": "Javascript and Ajax functionality", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://web2py.com/book/default/chapter/10"}, {"text": "ref1", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.web2py.com/AlterEgo/default/show/217"}, {"text": "ref2", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.web2pyslices.com/main/slices/take_slice/43"}, {"text": "ref3", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://web2py.com/book/default/chapter/05#HTML-Helpers"}, {"text": "ref4", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://web2py.com/book/default/chapter/05#Server-side-DOM-and-Parsing"}, {"text": "mailing list", "tag": "a", "pos": 2, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!forum/web2py"}]}], [{"text": ["A panel featuring several form library authors was presented at PyCon 2010, which might be relevant to your question:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": ["http://python.mirocommunity.org/video/1545/pycon-2010-panel-form-generato"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "http://python.mirocommunity.org/video/1545/pycon-2010-panel-form-generato", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://python.mirocommunity.org/video/1545/pycon-2010-panel-form-generato"}]}], [{"text": ["have you seen Bruno's django-floppyforms?", "It doesn't answer your question but it's worth being aware of it being done. "], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "django-floppyforms", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "https://github.com/brutasse/django-floppyforms"}]}], [{"text": ["I have recently used flatland to handle a complex form and found it to be very flexible.", "There's no widgets library, but it has a powerful HTML generator/filter, and as pointed out in the documentation, it's quite simple to write your own widgets.", "Don't let the \"0.0.2\" version fool you, the library is quite mature and stable."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "flatland", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://pypi.python.org/pypi/flatland"}, {"text": "pointed out", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://dag-flatland.readthedocs.org/en/latest/patterns/widgets/"}]}]]